Former French President Nicolas Sarkozy must face trial for illegal campaign financing after losing a court appeal on Thursday. The 'Bygmalion' scandal is just one of several legal problems facing Sarkozy following his unsuccessful re-election bid in 2012. Read more: Nicolas Sarkozy corruption charges reveal France's loose campaign finance practices Details of the case Other legal troubles: Sarkozy is also facing accusations of bribery and illegal influence. In 2014, Sarkozy allegedly obtained secret information from a lawyer general at the Court of Cassation through his legal counsel. He is also under investigation for allegedly accepting campaign financing in 2007 from then-Libyan ruler Muammar Gaddafi. Read more: Nicolas Sarkozy: Life is 'living hell' since Libya funding accusations Further appeal: Sarkozy's lawyers said their client would now take the case to the Cour de Cassation, France's court of final appeal. aw/rt (AFP, Reuters) Every evening at 1830 UTC, DW's editors send out a selection of the day's hard news and quality feature journalism. You can sign up to receive it directly here.